For each named physical EV charging host site carried from the parent task, identified by site name, location, and region, cover each of the {= evidence_role =} corroborating evidence roles listed below with a site-specific source (i.e. {= url =}+ URL under each role).

The corroborating evidence should show the physical host/site context, station/operator status, public registry/status data, and independent local or property context as separate public surfaces for the same site. A broad program page, all-sites table, locator landing, or station/status page can support only the role whose source context it visibly fits; it does not become host, registry, operator, and independent proof at once. It is not a host ranking, procurement recommendation, outreach list, contact search, lead score, installation recommendation, supplier comparison, or legal, engineering, safety, or compliance conclusion.

Evidence roles:
- `host_site_surface`: the side representing the physical site, property, parking facility, retail/fuel/travel-center location, public facility, or host/operator location surface itself.
- `station_operator_status`: the side representing a station-specific charger network, operator, official locator detail, or station page for the named site.
- `public_registry_status`: the side representing a public, utility, AFDC-style, government, or open station-data registry/detail surface for the named site.
- `independent_site_context`: the side representing an independent local, property, parking-authority, community, trade, or comparable third-party site-context surface for the named site, separate from the host page and station/registry pages.

Sites ought to be specific physical facilities or project locations, not charging networks, charging vendors, broad chains without a specific location, citywide or corridor-wide programs, generic eligibility pages, or broad public-property categories. Different addresses under the same chain count as distinct sites; alternate names for the same property, garage, mall, station, or project location count as the same site.

Requirements:
- The page must clearly identify the named physical site or a site/project at the same location. A generic chain page, citywide program page, public-incentive page, broad tracker page, or network landing page is not enough unless it names, addresses, table-entry-binds, or otherwise visibly singles out the specific named site/location.
- The page should make its evidence-role source fit visible: for `host_site_surface`, the page should read as a site-dedicated or host-controlled physical host, property, parking, retail, fuel/travel-center, public-facility, operator, tenant/location, or official location surface, not merely a public award/project/program list, multi-site EV charging inventory, locator page, all-sites table, or station-status page that names the site; for `station_operator_status`, the page should read as a station-dedicated charger-network, operator, official locator detail, or station page for the named site, not a broad network map, all-sites page, or program list; for `public_registry_status`, the page should read as a public, utility, government, AFDC-style, or open station-data registry/detail source for the named site, not a generic map landing or bulk network summary; for `independent_site_context`, the page should read as independent local, property, parking-authority, community, trade, or comparable third-party context for the named site, not the host page, charging-operator station page, public registry detail, broad NEVI/DOT/public-program list, or all-sites inventory.
- The page should expose a concrete role-scoped public fact about the site or charging station: for `host_site_surface`, a site-context, parking, access, amenity, location, host-identity, store/facility, or charging-context fact; for `station_operator_status`, a station operator, network, access, charger level, connector, port count, power, pricing, opening, live/planned/open/temporary status, or source-stated station metadata fact; for `public_registry_status`, a public registry or public-data fact such as station identity, network, access, charger type, connector, port count, fuel type, update date, or registry status; for `independent_site_context`, a separately sourced local/property/parking/community/trade fact tying the same physical site to EV charging context.
